found:\n\n1. **PR Scope**: This PR redesigns UI container components (UIPanel, U
IDialog, UIToast, UIAlert) and updates UIButton to align with PRD-004 and the de
sign spec for issue-19.\n\n2. **Key changes**:\n   - UIPanel.ts: Added show/hide
animations, overlay support, close button with UIIcon, removed default export\n 
 - UIDialog.ts: Now extends UIPanel, added closeOnOverlay, static alert() method
, hide animation before callbacks\n   - UIToast.ts: Added type color bar, ToastM
anager singleton, old API compatibility\n   - UIAlert.ts: New file with type col
or bar, show/hide animations\n   - UIButton.ts: Fixed interaction state machine 
(pointerdown/pointerup/pointerupoutside), added setTexture/setColors\n   - Tests
updated for all of these\n   - Designs/issue-19 files created as design artifact
s\n   - Documentation updated\n\nLet me now check for issues:\n\n**Blocking Issu
es:**\n\n1. **UIDialog design file vs implementation inconsistency in closeOnOve
rlay handling**:\n   - In `designs/issue-19/src/ui/UIDialog.ts`, the `onOverlayC
lick` is passed in `panelConfig` and uses `this.cancel()` in the arrow function 
BEFORE `super()` is called. This would fail because `this` is not available befo
re `super()`.\n   - In the actual implementation `apps/phaser3/src/ui/UIDialog.t
s`, this was fixed by passing `onOverlayClick: undefined` in panelConfig and bin
ding after `super()`. But there\'s still a potential issue: when `closeOnOverlay
=true`, it calls `this.overlay.off(\'pointerdown\')` then `this.overlay.on(\'poi
nterdown\', () => this.cancel())`. However, the UIPanel constructor already set 
up a `pointerdown` handler on the overlay that calls `onOverlayClick`. Since `on
OverlayClick` was set to `undefined` (actually `() => {}` after defaults), the o
riginal handler does nothing. The fix seems correct.\n\n2. **UIButton alpha valu
e**: PRD-004 section 3.1 and 3.6 says Disabled state must have `alpha ≤ 0.5`, bu
t UIButton uses `0.6`. The design spec `03-component.md` also says "Disabled: bg
Color（透明度 0.6）". Wait, looking at PRD-004 3.6: "DISABLED 态必须调用 disable
Interactive()，alpha ≤ 0.5". But the component doc 03-component.md says "Disable
d: bgColor（透明度 0.6）". There\'s an inconsistency in the project\'s own docs.
PRD-004 says ≤ 0.5, 03-component.md says 0.6. The implementation uses 0.6. This 
is a discrepancy but since 03-component.md explicitly documents 0.6, and the PRD
says ≤ 0.5, 0.6 violates the PRD. Let me mark this as Major.\n\n3. **UIToast sho
w() animation bug**: In the actual implementation `apps/phaser3/src/ui/UIToast.t
s`, `show()` does:\n   ```ts\n   this.scene.tweens.add({\n     targets: this,\n 
   alpha: 1,\n     y: this.baseY,\n     ...\n   });\n   ```\n   This is correct 
(uses `baseY`). But in `designs/issue-19/src/ui/UIToast.ts`, `show()` does:\n   
```ts\n   y: this.y - 20,\n   ```\n   Wait, in designs/issue-19, the constructor
sets `this.y += 20`, then show() tweens to `this.y - 20`. But `this.y` was alrea
dy mutated in the constructor! So the tween target would be the original y, not 
`this.y - 20`. Wait, let me re-read:\n   - Constructor: `this.y += 20` (so if ba
se y was 100, now it\'s 120)\n   - show(): `y: this.y - 20` (targets 100)\n   \n
  Actually this works because `this.y` is 120, and `this.y - 20` = 100. But wait
, if `show()` is called multiple times, the second time `this.y` is already 100 
(after the first tween), so `this.y - 20` would be 80, which is wrong!\n   \n   
The actual implementation fixed this by using `baseY`. The design file still has
the bug. But the design file is just documentation/artifact, not the actual code
. The actual code is correct.\n\n4. **UIAlert left bar height inconsistency**:\n
  - PRD-004 5.15 says: "增加左侧 4px 色条作为类型标识"\n   - `docs/design-docs/u
i-style-guide/03-component.md` section 3.7 says: "色条宽度必须为 4px", and the l
eft bar height in UIAlert should be `height - 4px` (line 98 in UIAlert.ts: `heig
ht - 4`).\n   - But in `designs/issue-19/design-spec.md` section 3.4: "左侧色条:
4px 宽，高度 height - 4px" for UIAlert, and for UIToast: "高度 height - 8px".\n 
 - The actual code matches: UIAlert uses `height - 4`, UIToast uses `height - 8`
. This is correct.\n\n5. **Missing `baseY` in designs/issue-19 UIAlert**:\n   - 
The designs/issue-19/src/ui/UIAlert.ts does NOT have `baseY`, it has the same bu
g as UIToast in designs: `this.y += 20` in constructor, then `y: this.y - 20` in
show(). Again, this is only in the design artifact, not actual code.\n\n6. **UIT
oast backward compatibility auto-show logic**:\n   ```ts\n   if (config.title ||
config.startTime) {\n     this.show();\n   }\n   ```\n   This means that if some
one creates a new-style Toast with only `message` and `type`, it will NOT auto-s
how. They must explicitly call `.show()`. This is a behavior change. Looking at 
PRD-004 5.11: "ToastManager 支持队列，避免多个 Toast 重叠". The static `UIToast.
show()` does call `toast.show()`. But direct `new UIToast()` without old params 
won\'t auto-show. The PRD doesn\'t specify whether `new UIToast()` should auto-s
how. However, the old implementation auto-showed. This could break existing code
that does `new UIToast(scene, {message: \'x\'})` expecting it to show. The backw
ard compatibility comment says "auto-show only when old API params are detected"
- this suggests the new API requires explicit show(). This is actually reasonabl
e for a redesign but could be considered a breaking change.\n\n7. **UIDialog con
firm/cancel button click handling**:\n   Looking at UIButton\'s setupInteraction
