    type='think',
    think='Let me now compile my findings and write the review report. Let me al
so check if there are any other issues I might have missed.\n\nKey findings:\n\n
**Blocking:**\n1. None that I can definitively identify as blocking. The code se
ems functionally correct.\n\n**Major:**\n1. **UIDialog design spec document cont
ains a critical `this` before `super()` bug**: `designs/issue-19/src/ui/UIDialog
.ts` line 62-65 has `onOverlayClick: () => { if (config.closeOnOverlay) { this.c
ancel(); } }` inside `panelConfig` which is passed to `super()`. This means `thi
s` is accessed before `super()` is called, which is a TypeScript/JavaScript runt
ime error. The actual implementation fixed this, but the design artifact (which 
serves as documentation) contains this bug. Since design specs are meant to be r
eferenced by future developers, this is a Major documentation issue.\n\n2. **UIT
oast and UIAlert design artifacts have `baseY` animation bug**: The design files
`designs/issue-19/src/ui/UIToast.ts` and `designs/issue-19/src/ui/UIAlert.ts` do
n\'t have `baseY`, so calling `show()` multiple times would drift the position. 
Again, actual code is fixed, but design docs are buggy.\n\n3. **UIAlert `show()`
animation duration mismatch with design spec**: The design spec `designs/issue-1
9/design-spec.md` section 3.4 says UIAlert show() should use `duration=200ms`, b
ut it also says `UITweens.popup.duration` which is 200ms. Looking at actual code
, it uses `UITweens.popup.duration` (200ms). Good.\n\n4. **UIButton disabled alp
ha = 0.6 violates PRD-004**: PRD-004 section 3.6 explicitly states "Disabled 态.
..alpha ≤ 0.5". UIButton uses 0.6. The `03-component.md` says 0.6, but PRD-004 i
s the higher-level requirement doc and says ≤ 0.5. This is a Major compliance is
sue.\n\n5. **ProgressToastManager loses custom `startY` for ToastManager**: The 
old code `new ToastManager(scene, startY)` passed `startY`, but `ToastManager.ge
tInstance(scene)` ignores any custom startY. This means if a caller passed a cus
tom `startY` to `ProgressToastManager`, the underlying `ToastManager` will still
use the default. However, `ProgressToastManager` computes Y positions itself (`y
= this.startY - this.manager.getCount() * this.spacing`), so the actual toast po
sitions might be correct. But the ToastManager\'s internal `startY` is used for 
repositioning after dismiss. When a toast is dismissed, `repositionToasts()` use
s `this.startY - index * this.spacing`. If ToastManager uses default while Progr
essToastManager uses custom, there could be misalignment. Wait, looking at Progr
essToastManager, it registers toasts with `manager.register(toast.getToast())`. 
The toast\'s Y is set by ProgressToastManager when creating it. But when a toast
is removed, ToastManager.repositionToasts() will recalculate Y based on its own 
startY, not ProgressToastManager\'s. This could cause misalignment if they have 
different startY values. This is a Major issue.\n\n6. **designs/issue-19/design-
spec.md warning color inconsistency**: The design spec says `UITheme.goldBrown` 
for warning, but actual code and updated style guide use `UITheme.warning` (0xff
aa00). The design artifact is inconsistent.\n\n7. **Missing `docs/frontend/ui-co
mponents.md` update**: PRD-004 9.3 requires `docs/frontend/ui-components.md` 已
重写为本 PRD 内容. The PR doesn\'t touch this file.\n\n8. **UIAlert test doesn\'
t test hide animation with onComplete**: The `hide()` test just calls `expectTwe
enCreated` but doesn\'t verify the component is destroyed. Not a big issue.\n\n9
. **ToastManager `register`/`unregister` old API compatibility**: The `register`
method wraps `dismiss` but doesn\'t call `show()`. If an external toast is regis
tered, it might not be shown. But this is old API compat.\n\n**Minor:**\n1. `exp
ort default` removed from files but trailing blank line added at end of some fil
es (UIPanel.ts, UIDialog.ts, UIAlert.ts, UIToast.ts have an extra blank line or 
missing final newline). Actually looking at the files, they end without a traili
ng newline after the closing brace, which is fine.\n\n2. **UIButton `setTexture`
doesn\'t handle label correctly when background is Image**: When `setTexture` is
called and `createBackground()` creates an Image, the label is removed and re-ad
ded. This is fine. But `createBackground()` doesn\'t set `this.originalFillAlpha
` for Image, which is fine since it\'s only used for Rectangle.\n\n3. **UIButton
`setColors` doesn\'t update `pressedColor`**: The method signature is `setColors
(bgColor, hoverColor, strokeColor)` but doesn\'t accept `pressedColor`. PRD-004 
5.3 says `setColors(bgColor, hoverColor, strokeColor)` so this matches the spec.
\n\n4. **UIAlert leftBar height inconsistency between PRD-004 and design spec**:
PRD-004 5.15 doesn\'t specify left bar height. Design spec says `height - 4px`. 
03-component.md says `height - 4px`. Code matches. Fine.\n\n5. **UIToast old API
compat `hide()` calls `dismiss()` which destroys the toast**: Old code `hide()` 
might not have destroyed. But this is acceptable for compatibility since old API
`markAsComplete` etc still work.\n\n6. **ToastManager constructor is private but
`getInstance` ignores custom `startY`**: Actually looking at the implementation,
`getInstance(scene)` always creates with default startY. If someone wants a cust
om startY, they can\'t use `getInstance`. But the old public constructor is now 
private. This is a breaking change for any code that did `new ToastManager(scene
, customY)`. However, the only usage in the repo was `ProgressToastManager` whic
h passed `startY`. Now that custom Y is lost.\n\nLet me verify if `ToastManager.
getInstance` can accept startY by reading the code again... No, it doesn\'t. The
signature is `static getInstance(scene: Scene): ToastManager`.\n\nWait, looking 
at `ProgressToastManager`:\n```ts\nconstructor(scene: Scene, startY?: number) {\
n    this.scene = scene;\n    this.startY = startY ?? scene.cameras.main.height 
- 100;\n    this.manager = ToastManager.getInstance(scene);\n}\n```\n\nIt stores
its own `startY` and uses it when creating toasts. But `ToastManager.register(to
ast)` adds the toast to `this.toasts`. When the toast is dismissed, `removeToast
` is called, then `repositionToasts()` uses `this.startY` from ToastManager, not
ProgressToastManager. Since ToastManager uses default `scene.cameras.main.height
- 100`, if ProgressToastManager used a custom startY, repositioning would be wro
ng.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at ProgressToastManager.show():\n```ts\n
show(config: ProgressToastConfig): ProgressToast {\n    const y = this.startY - 
this.manager.getCount() * this.spacing;\n    const toast = new ProgressToast(thi
s.scene, {\n      ...config,\n      y,\n      onComplete: () => {\n        this.
manager.unregister(toast.getToast());\n        config.onComplete?.();\n      },\
n    });\n    this.manager.register(toast.getToast());\n    return toast;\n}\n``
`\n\nThe toast\'s Y is set based on ProgressToastManager\'s startY and spacing (
80). But when it\'s registered with ToastManager, ToastManager thinks the toast 
is at some Y. When a toast dismisses, ToastManager.repositionToasts() does:\n```
ts\nthis.toasts.forEach((toast, index) => {\n    const targetY = this.startY - i
ndex * this.spacing;\n    ...\n});\n```\n\nToastManager\'s spacing is 64, and it
s startY is default. So if ProgressToastManager had a custom startY or spacing, 
the repositioning would be incorrect. This is definitely a bug, but whether it\'
s Major or Blocking depends on impact. Since ProgressToastManager is deprecated 
and the default values are the same (`height - 100`), it only affects custom sta
rtY cases. I\'ll mark it Major.\n\nLet me also check the `designs/issue-19/src/u
i/__tests__/setup.ts` to see if there are test utilities there.\n\nActually, I t
hink I have enough to write the report. Let me also quickly check if the `packag
e-lock.json` change is relevant - probably just a lockfile update from some depe
ndency.\n\nLet me now write the review report.',
